1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:11,600
<i> How's Grandma Isang?</i>

2
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:14,067
<i> Most likely it's dementia.</i>

3
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:17,800
<i>When Mom was robbed and killed,
I cried so hard.</i>

4
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:19,500
<i>I just stopped crying
when Grandma came</i>

5
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:20,700
<i> and hugged me.</i>

6
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:22,533
<i>Since then, Grandma
has been with me</i>

7
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:23,967
<i> in all our fights.</i>

8
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:26,167
<i>That's why it hurts me
to see her like this,</i>

9
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:28,700
<i>because I feel like
I can't be with her</i>

10
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:30,700
<i>in the fight
she is going through.</i>

11
00:00:30,833 --> 00:00:31,967
<i>- Vince?
- Where can I get...</i>

12
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:34,800
<i>- Vince!
- Oh, okay, I'll just go back.</i>

13
00:00:34,967 --> 00:00:35,900
<i> What happened?</i>

14
00:00:36,033 --> 00:00:36,900
<i> Faye...</i>

15
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:37,967
<i>You're putting
your love life first.</i>

16
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:39,667
<i> That love life it's dangerous.</i>

17
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:40,667
<i> Look at Dante.</i>

18
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:41,967
<i> He put his love life first</i>

19
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:43,367
<i> that's why he got killed.</i>

20
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:44,900
<i> I never told anyone.</i>

21
00:00:45,033 --> 00:00:46,933
<i>You said you didn't
tell anyone else, right?</i>

22
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:48,233
<i> How would he know that?</i>

23
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:49,700
<i> Why are we waiting here?</i>

24
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:51,233
<i> Dante has a relative</i>

25
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:53,233
<i> whom he told before he died</i>

26
00:00:53,367 --> 00:00:54,633
<i> who his boss really is.</i>

27
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:57,567
<i>Then you're going to give us
different addresses.</i>

28
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,533
<i>Once the syndicate goes
to that fake address,</i>

29
00:01:00,667 --> 00:01:01,667
<i> that's where we'll find out</i>

30
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:03,400
<i>who the traitor is here
at Station 12.</i>

31
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:04,433
<i> They're loaded.</i>

32
00:01:04,567 --> 00:01:05,967
<i>It seems my suspicions
weren't wrong.</i>

33
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,400
<i>Robles is the snake
of Station 12.</i>

34
00:01:13,533 --> 00:01:14,533
Hello, Boss?

35
00:01:14,667 --> 00:01:15,933
We're here already.

36
00:01:16,067 --> 00:01:17,400
All right, go in.

37
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:18,467
Hurry up!

38
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:20,067
All right, Boss.

39
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:36,167
Boss...

40
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:38,133
it looks like there's
no one in the house anymore.

41
00:01:38,267 --> 00:01:39,233
It looks like they've left.

42
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:40,700
What?

43
00:01:40,867 --> 00:01:41,800
Are you sure?

44
00:01:41,933 --> 00:01:42,600
Yes, Boss.

45
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:43,967
We've searched the entire house.

46
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:45,100
Nothing at all.

47
00:01:45,233 --> 00:01:46,667
Boss, it looks like
they got ahead of us.

48
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,200
<i>No, they're scheduled
to go there tomorrow.</i>

49
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:51,200
Maybe they just backed out.

50
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:52,933
All right, get out of there.

51
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:56,200
Let's go! Let's go!

52
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:04,100
What, Bok?

53
00:02:04,233 --> 00:02:05,333
What's our plan with Robles?

54
00:02:05,467 --> 00:02:07,700
Let's beat him up!
I'm getting pissed off.

55
00:02:07,833 --> 00:02:09,633
You know, he's the reason.

56
00:02:09,767 --> 00:02:12,567
It's his fault that people
look down on the police.

57
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:13,967
Because of people like him!

58
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:15,300
Just relax, Bok.

59
00:02:16,367 --> 00:02:18,100
I also want to give Robles
a lesson,

60
00:02:18,233 --> 00:02:19,167
but let's wait first.

61
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:20,233
Not now.

62
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:23,133
We need to find out first

63
00:02:23,267 --> 00:02:24,733
to whom he is reporting.

64
00:02:25,767 --> 00:02:27,100
And then what?

65
00:02:28,133 --> 00:02:29,867
Well, that's the time
we'll gang up on him.

66
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,733
That, I like that.

67
00:02:32,867 --> 00:02:35,167
But what,
what are we going to do

68
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:38,233
Now that we know
he's our enemy's puppet?

69
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:42,033
We've been waiting here
for a long time.

70
00:02:44,167 --> 00:02:46,067
It's been two hours.

71
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:48,833
It's better if we go back
to the station.

72
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:52,533
Later, Robles might notice that
this is just an entrapment.

73
00:02:53,833 --> 00:02:56,067
There are still no witnesses.

74
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:02,000
Robles, Robles...

75
00:03:37,167 --> 00:03:38,033
You know,

76
00:03:38,167 --> 00:03:39,267
if it wasn't for the Mayor,

77
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,500
Ma'am Sophia probably
did something to you.

78
00:03:41,633 --> 00:03:42,767
That's hard.

79
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:43,700
You're not together,

80
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:46,133
but your in-laws
are already hurting you.

81
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:48,700
That's why I don't want
to get married

82
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:49,800
because I don't want
to have in-laws.

83
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:53,733
Besides, no one wants
to marry you, Bro.

84
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,733
Are you trying
to be personal, Bro?

85
00:03:56,767 --> 00:03:58,933
Earlier, when I was trying
to get my birth certificate...

86
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:00,333
Oh?

87
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:02,333
I saw Faye.

88
00:04:02,467 --> 00:04:05,067
She called me,
but I ignored her.

89
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:09,867
That's because she's
with her brother.

90
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,067
Why?

91
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,667
What did Miss Faye
do wrong to you?

92
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:13,833
Yes, of course!

93
00:04:13,967 --> 00:04:15,533
You should tell Faye
what you're thinking.

94
00:04:15,667 --> 00:04:16,700
That's right!

95
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:18,733
So that what happened to you
doesn't happen again.

96
00:04:18,867 --> 00:04:20,967
I don't know, Bro.

97
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:23,767
It's okay for me
to be hurt, but...

98
00:04:23,900 --> 00:04:25,900
Later on,

99
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:28,700
Faye will be the one
who gets hurt because of me.

100
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:45,967
Bobby...

101
00:04:46,100 --> 00:04:48,267
your friend from the Fiscal
Office came earlier.

102
00:04:49,367 --> 00:04:51,100
Oh, yes, I talked to him.

103
00:04:51,233 --> 00:04:52,700
They said there's
a hearing scheduled

104
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:55,233
for the case filed
by Ma'am Sophia.

105
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:58,167
Oh, about your inheritance
from your father?

106
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:01,233
- Yes.
- Oh.

107
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:04,533
Isn't that hearing going
to take a long time?

108
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:06,433
Can you handle it, Bobby?

109
00:05:07,967 --> 00:05:09,467
Yes...

110
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,300
for Grandma.

111
00:05:15,533 --> 00:05:16,900
You know...

112
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:20,167
That's Grandma's
favorite breakfast.

113
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:23,733
I'm sorry.

114
00:05:23,867 --> 00:05:26,067
Just get used to my cooking.

115
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:29,200
You too,

116
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:33,367
let's share Grandma's chores
around the house.

117
00:05:37,967 --> 00:05:38,933
Bobby, I'll do it.

118
00:05:39,067 --> 00:05:41,133
No, I'll do it.

119
00:05:41,267 --> 00:05:42,600
I'll do it, I'll do it.

120
00:05:42,733 --> 00:05:44,667
Oh, Bobby...

121
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:47,867
we're just here, okay?

122
00:05:48,967 --> 00:05:51,733
Even though we are not
Grandma's real grandsons,

123
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:54,633
we won't neglect her.

124
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,667
You too, Bobby.

125
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,533
We won't neglect you.

126
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:06,167
Thank you.

127
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:15,733
Oh, go ahead!

128
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:19,033
Oh, come on,
you'd better go.

129
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:20,733
I'll take care of this.

130
00:06:20,867 --> 00:06:24,433
Oh, Mar, clean up that, okay?

131
00:06:24,567 --> 00:06:25,400
You too.

132
00:06:25,533 --> 00:06:27,567
Laundry.
We'll do the laundry.

133
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,333
- Okay?
- Yes.

134
00:06:29,467 --> 00:06:30,800
- Come on.
- Oh, let's go.

135
00:06:30,933 --> 00:06:32,633
For the Chairwoman.

136
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:33,733
For the Chairwoman.

137
00:06:33,867 --> 00:06:35,533
For Grandma!
Hey, that's for later!

138
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:37,133
Hey, you, let's go!

139
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,067
Boss,

140
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:59,733
they didn't confront any
witnesses last night.

141
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:01,733
Maybe they backed out.

142
00:07:01,867 --> 00:07:05,500
Do you think I'm paying you
for your excuses?

143
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,667
You better make sure!

144
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,600
Regan,

145
00:07:09,733 --> 00:07:12,000
aren't you ashamed of the Mayor?

146
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:13,500
Fix your report.

147
00:07:13,633 --> 00:07:15,033
It's incomplete.

148
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:19,067
You know, I really don't want
to be nosy.

149
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:21,633
Maybe later,
they'll suspect me too.

150
00:07:21,767 --> 00:07:23,633
You know, Robles...

151
00:07:24,667 --> 00:07:27,233
if you can't carry out

152
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:30,267
your job inside the station,

153
00:07:31,633 --> 00:07:33,233
tell me.

154
00:07:33,367 --> 00:07:35,533
We can easily find
a replacement.

155
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,433
You know, you talk like...

156
00:07:39,567 --> 00:07:41,833
as if you'd be more
useful than me.

157
00:07:42,433 --> 00:07:43,633
Maybe you're forgetting?

158
00:07:43,767 --> 00:07:46,100
You're useless because you're
bumming around

159
00:07:46,233 --> 00:07:47,867
because you're wanted, right?

160
00:07:48,033 --> 00:07:50,233
Mayor, excuse me, okay?

161
00:07:50,367 --> 00:07:53,133
Do you know? In our province,
there is a saying...

162
00:07:53,267 --> 00:07:55,933
if your palm itches,
there's money coming,

163
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:59,500
but if your fist becomes itchy.

164
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:01,000
There's a face that will be hit.

165
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,667
Shall we sweat it out?

166
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,333
So we can find out
who's useless?

167
00:08:05,467 --> 00:08:07,200
Okay, try it.

168
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:08,700
But if I make your mouth bleed,

169
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:10,500
don't cry, okay?

170
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:15,967
Are you sure?

171
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:21,067
It's Robles?

172
00:08:21,233 --> 00:08:23,200
We can't believe it
either, Chief.

173
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:25,000
He wanted to hit him last night.

174
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:27,533
That's right, Chief.

175
00:08:27,667 --> 00:08:29,067
I feel so betrayed!

176
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,833
I was so kind to that guy,

177
00:08:30,967 --> 00:08:32,900
and I was so humble to him,

178
00:08:33,033 --> 00:08:35,233
and then he treats us like this!

179
00:08:35,367 --> 00:08:36,567
<i> Look at Dante.</i>

180
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:37,967
<i> He put his love life first,</i>

181
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:39,800
<i> that's why he got killed.</i>

182
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:43,567
It makes me wonder...

183
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:46,900
when did he became an enemy.

184
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:49,033
Maybe from the start,

185
00:08:49,167 --> 00:08:50,867
the criminals paid him.

186
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,500
That's possible, Chief.

187
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:56,300
But we'll only know
the answer to that...

188
00:08:56,467 --> 00:08:57,300
when we find out,

189
00:08:57,433 --> 00:08:59,700
who is Robles' real Boss.

190
00:09:24,967 --> 00:09:26,500
That's enough!

191
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:35,700
If you two haven't finished
pissing each other off yet,

192
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:37,500
I'll finish you off.

193
00:09:40,867 --> 00:09:42,167
You, Robles,

194
00:09:42,300 --> 00:09:44,900
make sure no witnesses show up.

195
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:48,433
If not, I'll follow you
to Dante.

196
00:09:48,567 --> 00:09:50,133
Don't worry, Boss.

197
00:09:50,267 --> 00:09:53,067
I'll clean up all the mess
Dante left behind.

198
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,233
Conde,

199
00:10:22,367 --> 00:10:23,800
he must not know...

200
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:27,933
that we've discovered
his true colors.

201
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,100
He should be grateful

202
00:10:31,233 --> 00:10:32,567
that we still need
something from him,

203
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:35,233
otherwise I'll bury him
in the pot myself.

204
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:37,567
Bok, just calm down.

205
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:40,033
That'll ruin our strategy
even more.

206
00:10:40,167 --> 00:10:41,767
Later on, he might notice.

207
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:44,300
What's your plan, Conde?

208
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:49,767
How do you plan to start
the investigation on Robles?

209
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:52,700
It's unlikely for him
to leave a mess here

210
00:10:52,833 --> 00:10:54,233
at the station, Chief,

211
00:10:55,267 --> 00:10:57,267
But at his house,

212
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:59,367
maybe Garcia and I can sweep
something up there.

213
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:01,500
Oh, Chief...

214
00:11:01,633 --> 00:11:05,067
what if we wiretap his house?

215
00:11:06,867 --> 00:11:08,567
No way, That's illegal.

216
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:10,633
Everything we get,

217
00:11:10,767 --> 00:11:12,900
we can't use in Court.

218
00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:16,133
Chief, what Robles is doing
is also illegal.

219
00:11:16,267 --> 00:11:18,567
We're just fighting him fairly.

220
00:11:22,467 --> 00:11:24,133
Okay.

221
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:25,967
Take a look at his house,

222
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,167
and I'll take care of Robles.

223
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:30,133
I won't let him go home

224
00:11:30,267 --> 00:11:31,500
until you get back.

225
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:34,200
- Yes, Sir!
- Yes, Sir!

226
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:36,133
Good luck!

227
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:49,333
Vince...

228
00:11:49,467 --> 00:11:53,667
why won't you answer my calls?

229
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:54,967
You know,

230
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:56,500
if your dad were alive,

231
00:11:56,633 --> 00:12:00,133
he'd be mad that you were the
one chasing the man.

232
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:03,933
Mommy, the day after
Vince was beaten,

233
00:12:04,067 --> 00:12:07,067
he started to avoid me.

234
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,933
Do you have anything to do
with this?

235
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:13,200
Are you serious, Faye?

236
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:16,600
You're actually pointing
your finger at your mother?

237
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:19,567
I have nothing to do
with what you're saying.

238
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:23,100
And if the man you're talking
about was beaten,

239
00:12:23,233 --> 00:12:25,133
he's probably a bad guy.

240
00:12:25,267 --> 00:12:27,233
Have you ever thought of that?

241
00:12:27,367 --> 00:12:28,767
Vince is not a bad guy!

242
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:30,733
He left you hanging.

243
00:12:30,867 --> 00:12:32,900
What else do you call that?

244
00:12:44,067 --> 00:12:45,533
Oh, there you are.

245
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:46,433
Madam.

246
00:12:46,567 --> 00:12:48,367
Why does everyone blame me

247
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:51,167
when something bad
happens to them?

248
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:56,500
Oh, Madam, they know for
themselves that they are guilty.

249
00:12:56,633 --> 00:13:00,100
They just want you
as their escape goat.

250
00:13:00,233 --> 00:13:01,833
- Good answer.
- Right?

251
00:13:01,967 --> 00:13:04,267
Oh, by the way, Madam,

252
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,133
Attorney just called.

253
00:13:06,267 --> 00:13:08,367
Your court hearing for the case
of Sir Joaquin's will

254
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,700
is scheduled next week.

255
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:12,233
Okay...

256
00:13:14,300 --> 00:13:17,467
First, Bobby's grandmother got
sick,

257
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,733
and now, this.

258
00:13:19,867 --> 00:13:23,667
Fate is on my side, Cheka.

259
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:26,933
The oppressed are truly blessed.

260
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:59,433
Robles' house is really big,

261
00:13:59,567 --> 00:14:01,900
for a policeman's salary.

262
00:14:02,033 --> 00:14:04,400
Then he says he's alone here.

263
00:14:04,533 --> 00:14:07,433
That's his press release
at the station.

264
00:14:07,567 --> 00:14:10,300
Who knows, maybe he's living
with someone here?

265
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:11,567
Well...

266
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:14,233
my press release before was
Cecilia and I were together.

267
00:14:14,367 --> 00:14:17,700
But in the end,
someone got ahead of me.

268
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:19,700
Those press releases are
something else.

269
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:25,267
Do you want to drop the case?

270
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:27,200
Yes, Mayor.

271
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:31,600
I'd like to focus on
taking care of grandmother.

272
00:14:31,767 --> 00:14:33,600
I don't want the stress...

273
00:14:33,733 --> 00:14:36,233
from Ma'am Sophia
filing a case anymore.

274
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:39,967
Your Grandmother Isang
is a good person,

275
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:44,700
and I feel sorry
for her situation.

276
00:14:44,833 --> 00:14:46,133
But if you want to
drop the case,

277
00:14:46,267 --> 00:14:50,100
why didn't you just talk
to my mother herself?

278
00:14:50,233 --> 00:14:53,600
You know Ma'am Sophia
doesn't like me.

279
00:14:53,733 --> 00:14:58,400
That's why I really want
to talk to you, Mayor.

280
00:14:58,533 --> 00:14:59,933
Well, in that case,
as early as now,

281
00:15:00,067 --> 00:15:01,667
I'm just going to apologize
to you right now.

282
00:15:04,333 --> 00:15:06,867
You can't help me?

283
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,033
That's not what I meant.

284
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:11,933
What's this nonsense, Glen?

285
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:17,133
You said we had something
important to discuss.

286
00:15:17,267 --> 00:15:20,567
What's that bastard doing here?

287
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:36,667
Sit down, Robles.

288
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:44,133
Our bosses are reopening
an important case.

289
00:15:44,767 --> 00:15:50,033
And I want you to take the lead
because I trust you.

290
00:15:50,167 --> 00:15:52,300
Thank you, Sir.

291
00:15:52,433 --> 00:15:53,400
What's the update on...

292
00:15:53,533 --> 00:15:55,700
Tonyo and Garcia's appointment
earlier, Chief?

293
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:59,233
What's the news about
Dante Eusebio's relatives?

294
00:15:59,367 --> 00:16:00,600
Have they spoken to them?

295
00:16:00,733 --> 00:16:02,033
Oh...

296
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:04,133
he didn't come.

297
00:16:04,267 --> 00:16:05,733
Maybe he got scared,

298
00:16:05,867 --> 00:16:08,567
not ready to testify.

299
00:16:08,733 --> 00:16:11,200
I hope, Chief,
he won't be scared anymore.

300
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:14,167
And in case you need my help to
talk to him,

301
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:15,433
let me know.

302
00:16:15,567 --> 00:16:17,200
I can convince him.

303
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:21,333
Thank you, Robles.

304
00:16:21,467 --> 00:16:23,733
You're really trustworthy.

305
00:16:23,867 --> 00:16:24,767
Okay, Chief.

306
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:27,333
I'll study this case
at my house.

307
00:16:27,467 --> 00:16:28,967
You can't go home.

308
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:32,100
Stay here at the station.

309
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,433
Did I hear that right, Chief?

310
00:16:36,567 --> 00:16:38,300
I'm not allowed to go home?

311
00:16:42,633 --> 00:16:45,400
Anybody home? Anybody home?

312
00:16:45,533 --> 00:16:48,167
Hey, be careful, be careful.

313
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,533
I'm really a bastard,
Ma'am Sophia.

314
00:17:02,667 --> 00:17:07,467
But if you really want to insult
me, you can use other words.

315
00:17:09,433 --> 00:17:10,933
Mayor, this is what I'm saying,

316
00:17:11,067 --> 00:17:14,567
that's why I don't want
to talk to your mom.

317
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,867
I'm sorry.

318
00:17:16,033 --> 00:17:16,933
I'll go ahead.

319
00:17:17,067 --> 00:17:19,500
Just a moment, Bobby.

320
00:17:19,633 --> 00:17:21,633
I'm sorry I deceived you.

321
00:17:25,667 --> 00:17:28,867
Mom, we're all adults here.

322
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:33,133
I know you're angry with dad
because of what he did to you,

323
00:17:33,267 --> 00:17:36,633
but don't take your anger out
on Bobby.

324
00:17:40,433 --> 00:17:41,933
Bobby, you're the one who said,

325
00:17:42,067 --> 00:17:43,600
that you wanted
this issue to end

326
00:17:43,733 --> 00:17:46,600
so you can focus
on Grandmother Isang.

327
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,400
Now's your chance.

328
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:54,067
Mom, I'm sorry, okay?

329
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,567
This issue needs to end.

330
00:17:56,967 --> 00:18:00,167
I mean, how can the people of
Calabari trust me

331
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:03,067
if I can't fix my own family?

332
00:18:13,767 --> 00:18:17,333
Yes, because our bosses
want that report

333
00:18:17,467 --> 00:18:19,633
to be submitted within the day.

334
00:18:19,767 --> 00:18:21,900
But, Sir, I can study
this better at home.

335
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:23,467
There's no distraction there.

336
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:27,100
I know, but here, you can get
help, and that's from Dizon.

337
00:18:27,233 --> 00:18:28,733
Robles...

338
00:18:28,867 --> 00:18:30,933
that case is a priority,

339
00:18:31,067 --> 00:18:33,200
and if you fix that,

340
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:34,867
I'll give you leave.

341
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:38,567
Okay, Chief.

342
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,400
Okay.

343
00:18:49,167 --> 00:18:52,100
Ma'am Sophia, like I told Glen,

344
00:18:52,233 --> 00:18:55,400
I don't want to fight you
in court anymore.

345
00:18:55,567 --> 00:18:58,033
So you want the easy money?

346
00:18:58,167 --> 00:19:03,233
Well, five million
is five million.

347
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:07,767
It's not money I'm after but
peace, Ma'am Sophia.

348
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:09,500
So even if I don't get
any inheritance,

349
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:10,767
it's okay.

350
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:13,267
Then you'll talk to the media,

351
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,700
you'll say I oppressed you?

352
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,133
Why would I do that?

353
00:19:18,267 --> 00:19:21,067
I just said
I want peace of mind.

354
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:23,167
I don't want a headache anymore.

355
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:30,867
This is the reason why I want to
talk to you, Mayor.

356
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:33,267
Your mommy is very suspicious.

357
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:37,100
Ma'am Sophia...

358
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:40,933
when I found out that Mayor
Joaquin was my father,

359
00:19:41,067 --> 00:19:42,367
I didn't want anything to happen

360
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:44,667
but to just meet him.

361
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:47,300
I wanted to have at least a
little relationship

362
00:19:47,433 --> 00:19:49,300
with my father.

363
00:19:49,433 --> 00:19:50,267
I didn't ask him

364
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:53,000
to introduce me to you,

365
00:19:53,133 --> 00:19:55,833
to introduce me to people.

366
00:19:55,967 --> 00:19:57,067
Ma'am Sophia, I'm sorry

367
00:19:57,200 --> 00:20:00,000
if I messed up your family.

368
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:00,933
I don't care

369
00:20:01,067 --> 00:20:05,167
if I get an inheritance or not,

370
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:10,133
All I ask of you is that there
be no more lawsuits.

371
00:20:10,267 --> 00:20:12,567
My grandmother
is more important to me.

372
00:20:16,167 --> 00:20:18,200
Okay, Bobby.

373
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:19,933
Don't worry about it.

374
00:20:20,067 --> 00:20:22,400
We're dropping the case,

375
00:20:22,533 --> 00:20:25,833
and we're not contesting dad's
inheritance with you.

376
00:20:25,967 --> 00:20:27,700
No!

377
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,867
Glen, don't meddle here!

378
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:34,400
Mom, I'm the man of the house
now,

379
00:20:34,533 --> 00:20:36,567
and this is dad's request.

380
00:20:36,733 --> 00:20:38,967
This is his last will
and testament.

381
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:40,967
Let's just grant it.

382
00:20:45,567 --> 00:20:49,333
Bobby, I hope this settles
things,

383
00:20:49,467 --> 00:20:52,900
and I'll pray for
Grandmother Isang's health.

384
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:57,433
Thank you, Mayor.

385
00:21:01,467 --> 00:21:04,333
Can I call you Big Sister Bobby?

386
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:11,933
Go ahead, Mayor.

387
00:21:12,367 --> 00:21:13,667
I'll go first.

388
00:21:14,300 --> 00:21:16,267
Okay, Sister.

389
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,000
Be careful.

390
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,100
Bok, you know...

391
00:21:29,233 --> 00:21:32,767
between Selena and Cecilia,

392
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,033
It seems...

393
00:21:34,167 --> 00:21:37,767
it seems like I feel
differently about Selena.

394
00:21:37,900 --> 00:21:41,367
How do you know
if she's the one?

395
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,867
Bok, how about you?
With Bobby,

396
00:21:43,033 --> 00:21:45,233
do you think she's the one?

397
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,733
I hope so.

398
00:21:49,867 --> 00:21:51,867
Your answers are so short.

399
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:53,267
I'm sorry, Bok.

400
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,800
I'm doing something.

401
00:21:54,933 --> 00:21:56,600
Oh, sorry, sorry.

402
00:21:56,733 --> 00:21:57,767
Okay, okay, okay.

403
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,667
Just keep fiddling around there.

404
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:09,633
Hello, Chief?

405
00:22:09,767 --> 00:22:11,500
Seriously, I'm touched.

406
00:22:11,633 --> 00:22:12,533
Between me and Tonyo,

407
00:22:12,667 --> 00:22:15,067
you really chose to call me.

408
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,000
Tonyo's phone is on silent.

409
00:22:18,167 --> 00:22:20,900
Maybe Tonyo just doesn't want
to talk to you.

410
00:22:21,033 --> 00:22:22,600
No, I'm just just joking.

411
00:22:22,733 --> 00:22:25,000
You know, Garcia,
you're all jokes.

412
00:22:25,133 --> 00:22:27,233
What's the update?
What's the news?

413
00:22:27,367 --> 00:22:34,300
Oh, Tonyo's still messing around
at Robles' house.

414
00:22:34,433 --> 00:22:37,233
But, Chief, Robles
is something else.

415
00:22:37,367 --> 00:22:39,667
His house is big.

416
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:42,867
It looks like he's made a lot
of money from the syndicates.

417
00:22:44,767 --> 00:22:46,300
Oh, it's already open.

418
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:47,567
Chief,

419
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:50,167
we are able open his house.

420
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:52,533
Okay, okay.
Hurry up, okay?

421
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:54,433
<i> You know from the start,</i>

422
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:56,367
Robles wanted to go home.

423
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:59,700
So if I stop him again,
he might get noticed.

424
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:01,400
- Hurry up!
- Copy, copy, Chief.

425
00:23:01,533 --> 00:23:02,467
Don't worry.

426
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:04,933
This very day, we'll find out

427
00:23:05,067 --> 00:23:06,900
who Robles' boss is.

428
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:13,600
Okay, Chief.

429
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:25,433
What are you doing
in Robles' house, Conde?

430
00:23:43,133 --> 00:23:45,333
Where did Tonyo and Garcia go?

431
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:47,300
That's what I don't know, why?

432
00:23:47,433 --> 00:23:49,167
Your face is also thick, right?

433
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:51,533
You're meeting Conde
at your house.

434
00:23:51,667 --> 00:23:53,600
What are you talking about?
I'm here at the station.

435
00:23:53,733 --> 00:23:54,533
So what is Conde doing here

436
00:23:54,667 --> 00:23:55,900
- at your house?
- What?

437
00:23:56,067 --> 00:23:58,567
That red car,
I noticed it earlier.

438
00:23:58,700 --> 00:23:59,700
We arrived at the same time.

439
00:23:59,833 --> 00:24:01,267
Until now, it's still there.

440
00:24:03,533 --> 00:24:04,467
What are you doing?

441
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:05,533
Get out!

442
00:24:07,167 --> 00:24:08,233
Lieutenant Samson,
what's the news?

443
00:24:08,367 --> 00:24:09,333
There's a big mess here!

444
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:10,367
What mess?

445
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:12,367
It's Robles, he took
Major Flores hostage.

446
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:13,133
What?

447
00:24:13,267 --> 00:24:15,167
Am I going to continue my leave?

448
00:24:15,300 --> 00:24:16,167
What do you mean
you'll continue with it?

449
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:17,733
I'm going straight to resigning.

450
00:24:17,867 --> 00:24:18,800
- What?
- What?

451
00:24:18,933 --> 00:24:20,400
What's going on
with Robles, Tonyo?

452
00:24:20,533 --> 00:24:21,467
Why is he acting like this?

453
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:22,867
That can only mean one thing.

454
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,400
He found out that
we already know

455
00:24:24,533 --> 00:24:26,033
he's part of the syndicate.
